an from Thessalonica. The 16 manuscripts that transmit his encomium have been transcribed, collated, and carefully investigated, in order to reconstitute the manuscript transmission and prepare of a modern critical edition that enables important inferences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aByzantinische Hagiographie. 4aHeiligenenkomien. 4aSpäte Byzantinerzeit. 4aTheologie. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aByzantine Hagiography.  aEncomium.  aLate Byzantine Period.  aTheology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021z9783110753813oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311071148640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311071156140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110711561423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110711561/original  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1b2021  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021